  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Cyprus PR application is straightforward with fast processing—typically 2 months from submission to approval. The process can largely be handled remotely until you travel to collect your residence permit.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Select and Purchase Property</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Choose your property carefully—new development for standard route, or qualifying resale. Conduct due diligence on the developer and property. Sign the contract of sale and pay at least €200,000 deposit (remainder can be after approval). Property should be from a single development.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Open Cyprus Bank Account and Deposit €30,000</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Open an account with a major Cypriot bank (Bank of Cyprus, Hellenic Bank). Deposit €30,000 in a 3-year fixed term deposit. This shows financial stability and commitment. The bank will provide confirmation letter for your application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Required Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Prepare: valid passport, criminal record certificate (from country of residence and citizenship), proof of annual income (€30,000+ from abroad), marriage certificate (if applicable), children's birth certificates, health insurance certificate, CV/resume. Documents need apostille and certified translation to Greek.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Applications are submitted to the Civil Registry and Migration Department in Nicosia. Your lawyer typically handles submission. Pay the €500 application fee per person. You don't need to be present for submission—can be done by power of attorney.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Application Review (Fast-Track)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus processes investment-based PR applications on a fast-track basis—typically 2 months. The Ministry of Interior reviews documentation, conducts security checks, and verifies the investment. You may be asked for additional documents during this period.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Approval</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, you'll be notified (typically through your lawyer) that your PR has been granted. You have 1 year from approval to enter Cyprus and collect your residence permit. Pay the €70 permit issuance fee.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Travel to Cyprus and Collect Permit</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Enter Cyprus on your national passport (or visa-free if applicable). Visit the Civil Registry office with your passport and approval letter. Provide biometrics (photo, fingerprints). The physical PR card is typically ready in 1-2 weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Maintain Your Status</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Your PR is permanent as long as you: maintain the property investment, keep the bank deposit for 3 years (can release after), and visit Cyprus at least once every 2 years. There's no requirement to live in Cyprus full-time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Tax residency tip:</strong> To benefit from Cyprus's non-dom tax regime, you need to become tax resident (spend 183+ days in Cyprus, or 60+ days with other ties). PR alone doesn't make you tax resident. Plan your first year carefully if tax optimization is a goal—you may need to establish Cyprus as your center of vital interests.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

