  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Buying Property from Wrong Developer</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Not all developers or properties qualify for the PR program. Verify the development has proper permits, the developer has track record, and the property meets the "new from developer" requirement. Due diligence on the developer is essential—some have had delivery delays or quality issues.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Proof of Foreign Income</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus requires €30,000+ annual income from sources outside Cyprus. Employment contracts, pension statements, or investment income documentation must clearly show the foreign source. Rental income from properties abroad qualifies—get proper documentation from tenants or management companies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Outdated or Incorrect Criminal Records</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Criminal record certificates must be recent (typically within 6 months) and from all countries of residence/citizenship. Get certificates apostilled and translated. Some countries take weeks to issue—start early. Missing or outdated certificates delay applications significantly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting the Biennial Visit Requirement</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must visit Cyprus at least once every 2 years to maintain PR status. Mark your calendar. Missing this requirement can technically invalidate your PR. A short visit counts—even a long weekend maintains compliance. Keep passport stamps as evidence.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Misunderstanding Work Rights</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus investment PR does not allow you to work as an employee in Cyprus. You can manage your own investments, run your own company (if invested in shares), and work remotely for non-Cyprus employers. But you cannot take local employment. Understand this limitation before applying.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

